WEBVTT

00:09.948 --> 00:12.117
MAN (over radio):
Keep your eyes open.

00:14.369 --> 00:16.580
All right, guys, what do we got?

00:16.622 --> 00:17.914
It's quiet out there.

00:17.956 --> 00:19.458
(over radio):
Stand by.

00:19.499 --> 00:20.667
(indistinct radio transmission)

00:20.709 --> 00:23.545
Yeah, we, uh,
we better be ready.

00:23.587 --> 00:25.004
Yeah, I'm a man.

00:25.046 --> 00:27.299
Don't make it look like makeup.

00:28.389 --> 00:30.099
- (vehicle approaching)
- Car.

00:30.141 --> 00:31.726
Car.

00:31.768 --> 00:34.312
Is that guy one of ours?

00:34.354 --> 00:37.148
Look at the license plate.

00:37.190 --> 00:40.026
Looks like we got ourselves
an anus tart.

00:40.067 --> 00:43.780
NARRATOR: Tobias Funke
was on his way to reconnect

00:43.822 --> 00:45.699
with a daughter
he'd lost touch with.

00:45.740 --> 00:46.700
Hey, there.

00:46.741 --> 00:48.326
It's Big Daddy.

00:48.368 --> 00:51.454
I thought I'd try to call you
before I surprised you.

00:51.496 --> 00:54.749
Things are...
really looking up, and...

00:54.791 --> 00:55.667
(phone beeps)

00:55.709 --> 00:57.168
Hello? Oh, damn it.

00:57.210 --> 00:59.253
What Sudden Valley does
to these cell phones.

00:59.295 --> 01:00.380
Oops.

01:00.421 --> 01:02.215
Unbeknownst to Tobias, however,

01:02.256 --> 01:05.009
the Sudden Valley home
he was on his way to visit...

01:05.051 --> 01:06.927
Anus tart is turning
on Tracey Lane.

01:06.969 --> 01:09.389
...had been rented out
to a television crew.

01:09.430 --> 01:10.473
He's creeping up George Michael.

01:10.515 --> 01:11.891
All right, guys, let's entrap

01:11.932 --> 01:13.309
a local predator.

01:13.351 --> 01:14.728
Come on. Lowlife.

01:14.769 --> 01:16.813
We got to put
this piece of (bleep)...

01:16.855 --> 01:18.255
Who, what, when,
where, why and how.

01:18.272 --> 01:19.607
Who, what, where, when,
why and how.

01:19.649 --> 01:22.276
Who, what, when,
where, why and how.

01:24.028 --> 01:25.946
MAN (over radio): Anus tart is
approaching the portico.

01:25.988 --> 01:28.742
NARRATOR: Yes, Tobias was
finally about to get

01:28.783 --> 01:31.745
a starring role
on a hit TV show.

01:31.786 --> 01:35.122
Is there a little girl here
all by herself?

01:35.164 --> 01:37.124
BEARD: And now the story
of the awful people

01:37.166 --> 01:39.544
who are about to lose
everything, and the one newsman

01:39.586 --> 01:42.088
who had no choice but to
entrap them all together.

01:42.129 --> 01:46.092
It's John Beard's To Entrap
a Local Predator, "Supercreeps."

01:46.133 --> 01:48.177
NARRATOR:
Now the story of a family

01:48.219 --> 01:51.431
whose future
was abruptly cancelled,

01:51.472 --> 01:53.391
and the one son-in-law
who had no choice

01:53.433 --> 01:54.934
but to keep himself together.

01:58.157 --> 02:01.315
It's Tobias's
Arrested Development.

02:04.652 --> 02:09.407
Five years before Tobias was to
appear on John Beard's TV show,

02:09.449 --> 02:11.743
his acting career
was as washed up...

02:11.785 --> 02:13.745
- None taken.
- ...as his family...

02:13.787 --> 02:15.455
You are soaked to the bone.

02:15.496 --> 02:17.957
...and those men he was
touching for some reason.

02:17.998 --> 02:19.834
And his wife challenged him

02:19.876 --> 02:22.420
to reexamine the other parts
of his life as well.

02:22.462 --> 02:24.130
There's nothing
keeping us together.

02:24.171 --> 02:27.091
It's time to give up our dreams
if they're not working.

02:27.133 --> 02:28.885
You know, your acting career,

02:28.927 --> 02:31.512
this marriage
that everyone thinks is a sham

02:31.554 --> 02:32.639
because you're gay.

02:32.680 --> 02:34.307
I-I'm sorry.

02:34.348 --> 02:37.518
Everyone thinks I'm gay?

02:37.560 --> 02:41.940
Well, I mean, it's kind of
a running joke in the family.

02:41.981 --> 02:44.776
I mean, y-you know that, right?

02:44.818 --> 02:47.069
'Cause of the misleading way
you talk sometimes.

02:47.111 --> 02:50.364
Oh, you're saying the way I talk
makes me sound gay?

02:50.406 --> 02:51.658
(chuckles)
When in the last year

02:51.699 --> 02:54.243
have I said anything
remotely mis...

02:54.285 --> 02:56.995
♪ It's just a fallacy! ♪

02:57.037 --> 02:59.874
...leading? Is this because
I want to be an actor,

02:59.916 --> 03:01.584
and all the leading men
in Hollywood are gay?

03:01.626 --> 03:03.419
I don't think
that all the leading men

03:03.461 --> 03:04.504
in Hollywood are gay.

03:04.545 --> 03:06.046
- Oh, honey.
- (sighs)

03:06.088 --> 03:08.758
Look, we're chasing things
that aren't real.

03:08.800 --> 03:11.511
Maybe we need to go out there
and find out

03:11.552 --> 03:13.095
what we're meant to do.

03:13.137 --> 03:16.599
His wife was giving him
the cold shoulder.

03:16.641 --> 03:18.225
And after kissing it good-bye,

03:18.267 --> 03:22.146
he sat with her family,
feeling lost...

03:22.188 --> 03:25.023
Well, you look like I feel.

03:25.065 --> 03:26.943
...and very misunderstood.

03:26.985 --> 03:28.361
Gay?

03:28.402 --> 03:30.446
No, I...

03:30.488 --> 03:31.865
No.

03:31.906 --> 03:34.492
Tobias knew
it was time to find out

03:34.534 --> 03:35.734
what he was truly meant to do.

03:35.743 --> 03:37.829
So when he came across a book

03:37.871 --> 03:40.080
the universe
had placed in his path,

03:40.122 --> 03:41.415
he was open to its inspiration.

03:41.457 --> 03:43.543
Oh, they're still reading,
but...

03:43.584 --> 03:45.795
well, I guess I can
leave them some love.

03:45.837 --> 03:47.839
So he just took
"eat" and "pray."

03:49.841 --> 03:51.425
"Eat" was easy,

03:51.467 --> 03:54.804
although it provided
no cosmic answers for him.

03:54.846 --> 03:58.016
But it was the part about India
that really got to him.

03:58.057 --> 04:00.518
And so, like the heroine
of Eat, Pray,

04:00.560 --> 04:02.436
- Tobias decided
- Wait a minute.

04:02.478 --> 04:05.565
to get as far away
from his wife as possible.

04:07.149 --> 04:12.196
And so Tobias found himself
booking passage to India.

04:12.238 --> 04:14.991
And soon, he discovered
his wife was also

04:15.033 --> 04:16.951
preparing to go somewhere...

04:16.993 --> 04:18.911
- I think you have my suitcase.
- ...far away.

04:18.952 --> 04:20.914
(sighs)
I'm so sorry, Tobias.

04:20.954 --> 04:22.248
Look, I've already packed.

04:22.289 --> 04:23.249
Can I just use this one?

04:23.290 --> 04:25.084
Oh, what the heck.

04:25.125 --> 04:28.379
I guess having matching luggage
isn't so romantic anymore.

04:28.421 --> 04:30.048
And these romantic gestures are

04:30.089 --> 04:32.717
possibly why people think
I'm a homosexual.

04:32.759 --> 04:36.512
Well, it's time to correct
old misconceptions.

04:36.554 --> 04:38.932
And that is why
I'm making a new start.

04:38.973 --> 04:41.350
Oh, a new start.

04:41.392 --> 04:43.895
Filled with compassion and love.

04:43.937 --> 04:45.271
I like that.

04:45.312 --> 04:46.689
Well, I've already got
the license plate,

04:46.731 --> 04:47.815
so go cry in your pie!

04:47.857 --> 04:50.026
And so Tobias, hoping to

04:50.068 --> 04:54.154
"straighten out" his image,
set out on a new start,

04:54.196 --> 04:57.491
beginning with a trip
to the airport in an outfit

04:57.533 --> 04:59.786
he pretty much put together
himself.

04:59.827 --> 05:01.495
Well, I guess this is why

05:01.537 --> 05:02.956
you never see them
driving convertibles.

05:02.997 --> 05:04.457
I'll have to check on that one.

05:04.498 --> 05:06.542
But it certainly
wasn't embraced...

05:06.584 --> 05:07.919
Stay in your lane, anus tart!

05:07.961 --> 05:09.295
(bleep) anus tart!

05:09.336 --> 05:10.713
...by the local
Indian community.

05:10.755 --> 05:12.131
You have the true sense
of the oneness of all.

05:12.172 --> 05:14.759
And his quest
hit a bump early on,

05:14.801 --> 05:18.012
as he struggled to learn
the customs and gestures of

05:18.054 --> 05:20.014
- the culture he hoped to adopt.
- Oh, goddamn it!

05:20.056 --> 05:23.101
Am I the only one
who still dresses to fly?

05:23.142 --> 05:25.352
Well, there we go.

05:25.394 --> 05:26.729
India clean.

05:26.771 --> 05:28.147
(chuckles)

05:28.188 --> 05:29.774
Now, how did I...

05:29.816 --> 05:31.067
No. No.

05:31.109 --> 05:33.402
Unfortunately,
recreating the look

05:33.444 --> 05:35.237
- of the traditional Indian garb
- Are you finished? Oh.

05:35.279 --> 05:36.906
turned out to be more
difficult...

05:36.948 --> 05:38.828
I look like one of those
hot guys from Spartacus.

05:38.866 --> 05:42.036
...without the aid of Pradeep,
the helpful Indian salesman...

05:42.078 --> 05:44.246
I feel like there was
less up top.

05:44.288 --> 05:47.207
...at Bed, Bath & Beyond, who
helped him learn how to tie it.

05:47.249 --> 05:48.709
Ah, got it, okay.

05:48.751 --> 05:50.128
(choking)

05:52.046 --> 05:53.589
Yes, I actually
like this better.

05:53.631 --> 05:55.091
- (knocking)
- Yes?

05:57.510 --> 05:58.886
Canadian?

05:58.928 --> 06:00.554
No, I'm American.

06:00.596 --> 06:02.682
Oh, yeah. I'm Canadian.

06:02.723 --> 06:04.058
Oh. Sorry.

06:04.100 --> 06:05.977
But because it was
a long flight,

06:06.019 --> 06:08.688
he figured he'd wait a beat
on finding his true calling

06:08.729 --> 06:10.648
and watch something to
take his mind off Lindsay...

06:10.690 --> 06:13.067
How could they not have
Failure to Launch?

06:13.109 --> 06:15.193
...who he knew was far away
at the time.

06:15.235 --> 06:16.696
(groans)
Goddamn it.

06:17.905 --> 06:19.365
And after taking

06:19.406 --> 06:20.950
the wrong bag at the airport...

06:20.992 --> 06:22.576
WOMAN (over P.A.): Do not leave
any goats unattended.

06:22.618 --> 06:25.997
All unattended goats
will be confiscated.

06:26.039 --> 06:28.374
...Tobias finally arrived...

06:28.415 --> 06:31.002
And so Tobias Funke
embarked on a--

06:31.044 --> 06:34.714
Oh, dear, Lord, it's... hot!

06:34.755 --> 06:37.633
...in India, yes, where he was
very uncomfortable.

06:37.675 --> 06:39.927
Not only because
the wind whipped up

06:39.969 --> 06:42.138
his queen-sized
fitted mini-sarong,

06:42.180 --> 06:44.974
but because he looked
the wrong direction

06:45.016 --> 06:46.216
when stepping into the street.

06:46.224 --> 06:47.434
(tires screeching)

06:47.476 --> 06:49.520
And so Tobias experienced India

06:49.562 --> 06:51.522
from the inside
of a hospital room,

06:51.564 --> 06:53.024
where the staff
was being trained...

06:53.066 --> 06:54.984
This man here broke his skull
in two places.

06:55.026 --> 06:57.277
...by the same doctor
he'd had in America.

06:57.319 --> 06:59.446
Once outside the airport
and once in the elevator

06:59.488 --> 07:02.240
when his sheet got caught and
he was pulled off his gurney.

07:02.282 --> 07:03.409
Literally.

07:03.450 --> 07:04.730
- (laughter)
- Two places indeed.

07:04.744 --> 07:06.328
This is very funny.

07:06.370 --> 07:08.122
It's like that new show
we just caught, Laugh-In.

07:08.164 --> 07:09.456
My name is...

07:09.498 --> 07:11.084
Oh!

07:11.125 --> 07:14.420
Now I've broken my skull
in a third place!

07:14.461 --> 07:17.090
On this elephant guy statue!

07:17.131 --> 07:19.800
Tobias had wanted the universe
to provide him a sign.

07:19.842 --> 07:21.552
You should be a comedy actor.

07:21.594 --> 07:23.721
And finally it had.

07:23.763 --> 07:25.765
This is the sign I've been...
(groans)

07:25.806 --> 07:27.975
Looking for.

07:28.017 --> 07:29.894
And after two more weeks
in the hospital,

07:29.936 --> 07:32.105
it was time
for his flight home.

07:32.146 --> 07:34.023
And that's when he got
another sign.

07:34.065 --> 07:35.983
(cell phone ringing)

07:36.025 --> 07:38.569
A call from Lindsay.

07:38.611 --> 07:40.362
Although he wouldn't be able
to reach the phone for hours...

07:40.404 --> 07:42.073
I'm ready to make this work.

07:42.115 --> 07:44.408
...due to his already
weakened spine.

07:44.450 --> 07:45.743
(bell chimes)

07:48.121 --> 07:49.622
NARRATOR:
Tobias and Lindsay

07:49.663 --> 07:51.498
shared the news
of their new start

07:51.540 --> 07:52.917
at a family gathering.

07:52.959 --> 07:54.585
I got the part.

07:54.627 --> 07:56.796
You know, it's funny,
for I, too, find that

07:56.837 --> 07:58.214
I am on a journey.

07:58.256 --> 07:59.548
Although, as we discovered

07:59.590 --> 08:01.467
when our MasterCard bill
came back,

08:01.508 --> 08:03.052
it was the same one she took.

08:03.094 --> 08:04.887
But mine has confirmed
that I should

08:04.929 --> 08:07.306
redouble my efforts to achieve

08:07.347 --> 08:11.269
the unachievable dream
of being an actor.

08:11.310 --> 08:14.105
A journey
that has left me eager

08:14.147 --> 08:17.775
to connect with my true love.

08:17.817 --> 08:20.027
Particularly if she finds her...

08:20.069 --> 08:22.780
way clear to covering
a 2, 000-rupee

08:22.822 --> 08:25.950
City of Hopelessness
hospital debt.

08:25.992 --> 08:28.119
The trick is going to be
getting anyone to believe

08:28.161 --> 08:29.411
that her husband
is straight enough

08:29.453 --> 08:31.330
to have a true love
that's a woman.

08:31.371 --> 08:33.082
What are you implying?

08:33.124 --> 08:35.126
Oh, I don't think there was
any implying going on at all.

08:35.168 --> 08:36.335
Didn't hear any implying.

08:36.376 --> 08:37.544
I wasn't implying.

08:37.586 --> 08:38.921
I'm sorry, Mother.

08:38.962 --> 08:40.506
It's just, I've got
a bit of a stick

08:40.547 --> 08:42.008
up my "bunghole"
about what I've now found

08:42.049 --> 08:43.467
is a running joke about me.

08:43.509 --> 08:45.303
But let's be honest.

08:45.344 --> 08:48.931
For 2, 000 rupees, we'd both
go down on Matthew McConaughey.

08:48.973 --> 08:50.808
(chuckles):
Yes, Michael?

08:50.850 --> 08:52.852
At the time of this
family meeting,

08:52.893 --> 08:54.061
2, 000 rupees was $36.

08:54.103 --> 08:56.022
I wouldn't.

08:56.063 --> 08:58.107
GEORGE SR.:
Of course you wouldn't, Michael.

08:58.149 --> 09:00.109
You never accept help
from anyone.

09:00.151 --> 09:02.402
And hoping to do things
differently this time,

09:02.444 --> 09:05.281
Lindsay immediately started
spending money she didn't have.

09:05.323 --> 09:06.907
JAMES:
Are you ready to make a move?

09:06.949 --> 09:11.537
As you can see,
I'm ready for a lot that's new.

09:11.578 --> 09:13.039
Oh, good heavens.

09:13.080 --> 09:15.041
While Tobias pursued

09:15.082 --> 09:17.043
the life of
a professional actor.

09:17.084 --> 09:19.086
Listen, I'm an actor,
you're an agent.

09:19.128 --> 09:20.213
You do the math.

09:20.254 --> 09:21.714
I want you to represent me.

09:21.755 --> 09:23.924
In other words,
you do the math--

09:23.966 --> 09:25.343
the money, the negotiating.

09:25.384 --> 09:27.427
You know I'm not
that kind of agent, right?

09:27.469 --> 09:29.055
I'm a real estate agent.

09:29.096 --> 09:31.807
I'm a predator; I sell
giant houses to very poor people

09:31.849 --> 09:33.559
who can't afford them
with predatory loans.

09:33.600 --> 09:35.519
No, see, that's the money stuff
I don't understand.

09:35.561 --> 09:37.437
All you need to do
is tell people

09:37.479 --> 09:39.523
what a terrific actor I am,
'cause I can't do it believably.

09:39.565 --> 09:40.900
What do you say?

09:40.941 --> 09:42.651
Sounds like it shouldn't be
too much work.

09:42.693 --> 09:43.819
(laughs):
Huzzah!

09:43.861 --> 09:45.071
Okay, here's the number

09:45.112 --> 09:47.114
of my current agent
Mike Matthews.

09:47.156 --> 09:50.201
He's at Allstate. Fire him.

09:50.243 --> 09:54.205
Tobias started seeing positive
career signs everywhere...

09:54.247 --> 09:55.622
...decorating my quarters.

09:55.664 --> 09:59.085
...he chose to put them.

09:59.126 --> 10:00.920
And at his new agent's
suggestion...

10:00.961 --> 10:02.838
Hi. I'm after pending.

10:02.880 --> 10:05.465
...he even snuck on to a studio
lot to hand out head shots

10:05.507 --> 10:08.719
to extras and other
show business insiders.

10:08.761 --> 10:10.388
Taft-Hartley pending.

10:10.429 --> 10:12.139
Things were
looking up for the Funkes.

10:12.181 --> 10:14.516
They even celebrated
their first

10:14.558 --> 10:16.769
- home-cooked Thanksgiving.
- Including duck l'orange.

10:16.810 --> 10:18.062
- (duck quacking)
- Oh!

10:18.104 --> 10:19.980
- Oh, no!
- (Lindsay screams)

10:20.022 --> 10:22.316
Lindsay!
Lindsay, get the scooper!

10:22.358 --> 10:23.692
Throw oranges at it.

10:23.734 --> 10:25.652
- Hot orange! Hot orange.
- (duck quacking)

10:25.694 --> 10:26.946
All right...

10:26.987 --> 10:28.572
It's throwing its voice!

10:28.614 --> 10:30.157
- MAEBY: Oh!
- TOBIAS: Lindsay!

10:31.325 --> 10:33.411
And so they went

10:33.452 --> 10:36.163
to the Fountain Valley
China Garden instead.

10:36.205 --> 10:39.375
And if the collapse
of the housing market,

10:39.417 --> 10:41.835
- his lack of auditions...
- Tobias Funke.

10:41.877 --> 10:43.796
or even the writers' strike

10:43.837 --> 10:45.881
couldn't deter Tobias
from his dream,

10:45.923 --> 10:47.841
the suicide of his ruined

10:47.883 --> 10:49.843
and despondent agent
certainly could.

10:49.885 --> 10:54.140
I believe he died as a warning,
in a way, his message perhaps

10:54.181 --> 10:56.183
to live within our means

10:56.225 --> 10:59.019
and be realistic
about our lives.

10:59.061 --> 11:00.604
And yet it didn't.

11:00.646 --> 11:03.065
Well, then I shall
redouble my efforts

11:03.107 --> 11:05.943
- so that he died in vain.
- (others gasp)

11:06.902 --> 11:08.279
(stammers)

11:08.321 --> 11:10.030
Meaning he will have led
a pointless life,

11:10.072 --> 11:11.157
is what I mean.

11:11.198 --> 11:12.450
Yes, carry on. Thank you.

11:12.490 --> 11:13.867
And he soon found himself

11:13.909 --> 11:17.288
bringing his wife
to an acting class

11:17.330 --> 11:19.915
in an effort to jump-start
his career and marriage.

11:19.957 --> 11:21.792
If everyone's good,
you'll get your juice.

11:21.834 --> 11:24.337
What did you say the name
of this acting class was again?

11:24.378 --> 11:25.838
Method One Clinic.

11:25.879 --> 11:27.399
LINDSAY:
Okay, I'm gonna go get coffee.

11:27.423 --> 11:30.550
Garden Grove Method One Clinic.

11:30.592 --> 11:32.428
And Tobias found himself
captivated

11:32.470 --> 11:34.096
by one of the monologues.

11:34.138 --> 11:36.807
And I made it in that movie,
the Fantastic Four,

11:36.849 --> 11:39.685
uh, but it wasn't fantastic
for me.

11:39.726 --> 11:41.645
Uh, I got carried away.

11:41.687 --> 11:44.231
And I'm like,
"This (bleep) is (bleep) up,

11:44.273 --> 11:46.692
"and I've got to get
my (bleep) together

11:46.733 --> 11:48.819
or I'm gonna be (bleep), too."

11:48.861 --> 11:51.322
Anyways, now I'm sober,
and I'm trying.

11:51.364 --> 11:53.199
It's... super hard.

11:53.240 --> 11:54.700
- (groans)
- (applause)

11:54.741 --> 11:56.243
Thank you. Thank you.

11:56.285 --> 11:58.536
It was a devastating
and personal story.

11:58.578 --> 12:00.247
Okay, notes:

12:00.289 --> 12:02.416
um, first of all, it seemed
you were slurring a bit there,

12:02.458 --> 12:04.918
and I just think
you'd have so much more fun

12:04.960 --> 12:06.420
