of show business big shots

17:09.807 --> 17:11.266
seeking plastic surgery.

17:11.308 --> 17:13.393
We're both actors!

17:13.435 --> 17:15.479
(loud, exaggerated sobbing)

17:18.565 --> 17:20.526
NARRATOR:
On the day of Lucille's trial,

17:20.567 --> 17:22.819
Tobias was in a hospital
with a woman

17:22.861 --> 17:25.531
he'd both fallen for
and had rushed into an ICU.

17:25.571 --> 17:28.282
See? Makeup makes everyone
feel a little better.

17:28.325 --> 17:29.785
You didn't leave me.

17:29.827 --> 17:31.704
Everybody leaves me.

17:31.745 --> 17:35.499
I've been left in Dumpsters
and on a curb and...

17:35.541 --> 17:37.042
Oh, I wouldn't dream of it.

17:37.083 --> 17:39.461
Excuse me. Could you, uh,
leave us alone for...

17:39.503 --> 17:41.213
- Yeah, absolutely, yes.
- Thank you.

17:41.254 --> 17:43.507
Oh, no, I-I'd like him
to-to stay.

17:43.549 --> 17:44.591
- Really?
- Yeah.

17:44.633 --> 17:45.592
Okay.

17:45.634 --> 17:46.885
I'm afraid that you have

17:46.926 --> 17:48.804
tested positive
for chlamydia, syphilis,

17:48.846 --> 17:50.263
gonorrhea, hepatitis,
pancreatitis,

17:50.305 --> 17:53.600
trichomonitis,
nongonococcal urethritis.

17:53.642 --> 17:56.562
All the itises, really,
and there's also

17:56.603 --> 17:57.813
a host of osises.

17:57.855 --> 17:59.565
Now, what this means
in nonmedical terms

17:59.606 --> 18:02.526
is that you have landed, uh,
a real party girl.

18:02.568 --> 18:04.444
TOBIAS:
Well, will she be okay?

18:04.486 --> 18:06.154
Well, we can treat
all of these things,

18:06.196 --> 18:07.823
but if she's really
gonna be okay,

18:07.865 --> 18:09.825
uh, she's gonna have to tackle
this drug problem.

18:09.867 --> 18:12.077
You didn't tell me
you had a drug problem.

18:12.118 --> 18:14.287
We met at a methadone clinic.

18:14.329 --> 18:15.288
Are you high?

18:15.330 --> 18:16.749
We met at an acting class.

18:16.790 --> 18:18.500
The Method One...

18:18.542 --> 18:21.211
There it is. I'm gonna let
you guys, uh, hash this out.

18:21.253 --> 18:23.296
I guess I shouldn't have
lied about being clean

18:23.338 --> 18:26.550
when I took that methadone,
but I'll do better this time.

18:26.592 --> 18:27.885
Or are you gonna leave me

18:27.926 --> 18:30.095
now that you know
that I'm a druggie?

18:30.136 --> 18:33.432
DeBrie, look, some people
struggle with addiction,

18:33.473 --> 18:36.059
other people are incapable
of ever being nude.

18:36.101 --> 18:37.603
Everybody has something.

18:37.644 --> 18:40.647
And it's my professional opinion
that your drug use

18:40.689 --> 18:44.610
is a direct result of your
abandoning your dream of acting.

18:44.651 --> 18:46.403
You are a gifted actress.

18:46.445 --> 18:48.405
When I first saw Straight Bait,

18:48.447 --> 18:49.740
there were two men making love,

18:49.782 --> 18:51.784
but I couldn't take
my eyes off of you.

18:51.825 --> 18:53.535
You watched Straight Bait?

18:53.577 --> 18:55.078
Oh, just2, 4and9.

18:55.120 --> 18:57.497
You were with a guy
who didn't care about you.

18:57.539 --> 19:00.751
But stick with me,
and I'll make you famous.

19:00.793 --> 19:04.504
By cashing in
on your most celebrated role.

19:04.546 --> 19:05.672
Come one, come all!

19:05.714 --> 19:08.133
Get your photo taken
with Sue Storm

19:08.174 --> 19:09.635
from the Fantastic Four!

19:09.676 --> 19:11.261
Hey, is that Jessica Alba?

19:11.303 --> 19:14.180
No, this is the original
Sue Storm, DeBrie Bardeaux!

19:14.222 --> 19:16.099
- Who?
- The original Sue Storm,

19:16.141 --> 19:17.726
DeBrie Bardeaux. She--
No, no!

19:17.768 --> 19:18.727
No free pictures, kids!

19:18.769 --> 19:19.728
No, no, scram!

19:19.770 --> 19:20.771
Get out of here! Go!

19:20.813 --> 19:22.105
Go, get out of here.

19:22.147 --> 19:23.649
I don't think this is working.

19:23.690 --> 19:26.025
Maybe I need to get
a regular job.

19:26.067 --> 19:28.194
I do have a law degree.

19:28.236 --> 19:30.071
I know, I know,
and I'm a doctor.

19:30.113 --> 19:32.031
But no, let's not settle.

19:32.073 --> 19:34.033
Look, it's the Fantastic Four.

19:34.075 --> 19:36.578
No one recognizes one alone.

19:36.620 --> 19:37.955
I've got an idea.

19:37.996 --> 19:40.081
Ten dollars gets you
a picture with

19:40.123 --> 19:41.333
real Hollywood characters!

19:41.374 --> 19:42.542
What do you say? Ten dollars.

19:42.584 --> 19:43.543
That's certainly cheap.

19:43.585 --> 19:45.796
Oh! Hello, young man,

19:45.838 --> 19:48.089
and his... uncle? Neighbor?

19:48.131 --> 19:49.382
Father.

19:49.424 --> 19:50.676
Oh! That's terrific.

19:50.717 --> 19:52.093
(laughs)
Well, how would you like

19:52.135 --> 19:53.470
to have your picture taken

19:53.512 --> 19:56.348
with real Hollywood
movie land characters?

19:56.389 --> 19:57.766
Are you the Smurfs?

19:57.808 --> 19:59.351
No, no, no.

19:59.392 --> 20:00.936
They're the Ambiguously Gay Duo.

20:00.978 --> 20:02.270
Oh, I assure you,

20:02.312 --> 20:04.105
there's nothing ambiguous
about me.

20:04.147 --> 20:06.399
I'm Johnny Storm,
the human flamer.

20:06.441 --> 20:10.236
And this is Sue Storm, my sister
and fellow fighter-in-law.

20:10.278 --> 20:12.405
Now watch as I get--
no, I have special effects!

20:12.447 --> 20:14.282
Look, children love fire.

20:14.324 --> 20:15.325
Oh.

20:15.367 --> 20:16.326
This isn't working either.

20:16.368 --> 20:17.995
(sighs)
You're right.

20:18.036 --> 20:20.455
Two people in blue
doesn't say Fantastic Four.

20:20.497 --> 20:22.165
You know what though?

20:22.207 --> 20:24.250
I think I may have
just the thing.

20:24.292 --> 20:25.460
Oh?

20:25.502 --> 20:27.546
Just "the thing."

20:27.587 --> 20:29.006
Cut to...

20:29.047 --> 20:31.591
Now that I'm the iconic
rock man The Thing,

20:31.633 --> 20:33.218
no one will misunderstand.

20:33.259 --> 20:35.971
I'm sure the Blues Brothers here
will know who we are.

20:36.013 --> 20:37.848
Excuse me, are you Sue Storm
and The Thing?

20:37.890 --> 20:39.683
Oh, who's smart now?

20:39.725 --> 20:41.393
Indeed we are.

20:41.434 --> 20:43.520
In fact, they were orthodox
members of the law firm

20:43.562 --> 20:46.231
Feinberg, Feinberg, Feinberg
& Feinberg.

20:46.272 --> 20:48.984
We represent Stan Lee
and Marvel Enterprises.

20:49.026 --> 20:50.652
This is a cease and desist

20:50.694 --> 20:52.445
ordering you
to stop impersonating

20:52.487 --> 20:54.113
any of our trademark characters.

20:54.155 --> 20:55.615
Oh, let me take a look at that.

20:55.657 --> 20:56.700
I have a law degree.

20:56.742 --> 20:57.910
No, DeBrie, I've got this.

20:57.951 --> 21:00.119
Mr. Feinberg?

21:00.161 --> 21:01.788
Uh, would it change your mind

21:01.830 --> 21:05.876
if I offered you
a free Sue Storm armband?

21:05.918 --> 21:07.794
It did not change his mind.

21:07.836 --> 21:10.547
And although the hate crime
charges were dismissed,

21:10.589 --> 21:12.298
they were told
they could not continue

21:12.340 --> 21:13.800
to pose as the Fantastic Four.

21:13.842 --> 21:16.553
Can they really make us leave
Hollywood Boulevard?

21:16.595 --> 21:19.681
Well, apparently in
this instance, paper beats rock.

21:19.723 --> 21:20.682
You have a rock?

21:20.724 --> 21:23.018
No, I am your rock now.

21:23.060 --> 21:24.061
Oh.

21:24.102 --> 21:25.228
So what are we gonna do

21:25.270 --> 21:26.939
now that we don't
have the rights?

21:26.980 --> 21:28.732
Well, we just go off-brand.

21:28.774 --> 21:32.318
Uh, we'll just change the names
and do a cheap generic knockoff.

21:32.360 --> 21:34.112
Kids don't care.

21:34.153 --> 21:35.864
Tobias took them down
to a street

21:35.906 --> 21:38.575
near Harbor Boulevard,
where his friend Gary Goose

21:38.617 --> 21:40.159
told him
they didn't police very much.

21:40.201 --> 21:42.081
Rock Monster and Ability
to Be Invisible Person.

21:42.120 --> 21:43.705
Hello, young man.
What brings you

21:43.747 --> 21:46.666
to at least 500 feet
past the entrance of Disneyland?

21:46.708 --> 21:47.834
Dad, can I get my picture taken

21:47.876 --> 21:49.002
with The Thing
and Invisible Girl?

21:49.044 --> 21:50.545
They're the Fantastic Four.

21:50.587 --> 21:52.547
Well, actually, technically,
I'm Rock Monster,

21:52.589 --> 21:54.883
and this is
Ability to Be Invisible Person.

21:54.925 --> 21:56.802
- Hey, you guys want the ten dollars or not?
- Yeah.

21:56.843 --> 21:58.344
- Uh...
- Yeah, yeah.

21:58.386 --> 22:00.055
Yes. Okay.

22:00.097 --> 22:02.641
We're The Thing
and the Invisible Girl.

22:02.682 --> 22:03.767
- You're under arrest.
- What?

22:03.809 --> 22:05.310
Boom. Turn around.

22:05.351 --> 22:06.686
- Let's go.
- I didn't...

22:06.728 --> 22:08.105
- Let's go. Get up there.
- Oh! Oh!

22:08.146 --> 22:09.898
Come on.

22:09.940 --> 22:11.900
- Oh, come on, now.
- (chuckles): No, no, no.

22:11.942 --> 22:14.319
We're not gonna kill him,
we're just gonna handcuff him.

22:14.360 --> 22:15.946
You can't shoot us
'cause it's not a felony.

22:15.988 --> 22:18.073
Keep your eyes on her.
I'll be right back.

22:18.115 --> 22:20.075
Okay.

22:22.494 --> 22:23.787
DeBRIE:
If it happens again,

22:23.829 --> 22:25.914
you know, it will be
a third strike.

22:25.956 --> 22:27.624
Three-strikes law's up for
review in the appellate courts,

22:27.666 --> 22:28.959
but we really
shouldn't be charging.

22:29.001 --> 22:30.710
I know of a street
in Garden Grove

22:30.752 --> 22:32.712
- where they don't police very much.
- Okay.

22:32.754 --> 22:34.255
NARRATOR:
Things were looking down.

22:34.297 --> 22:36.925
And over the following weeks,

22:36.967 --> 22:38.760
