23:14.838 --> 23:16.715
And that's when he heard
what sounded like two ostriches

23:16.756 --> 23:18.842
making love to a pop hit.

23:18.884 --> 23:20.552
But was actually this.

23:20.593 --> 23:24.097
♪ Why don't you
go away, go away ♪

23:24.139 --> 23:25.640
♪ Get away, get away ♪

23:25.682 --> 23:27.600
♪ Stay away ♪

23:27.642 --> 23:30.187
♪ You're hopelessly
hopeless... ♪

23:30.227 --> 23:32.605
(screams)
Good bird.

23:32.647 --> 23:34.191
- (screams)
- (ostrich squawking)

23:34.231 --> 23:35.650
Stop it, chicken!

23:35.692 --> 23:37.861
Somebody help!

23:37.903 --> 23:39.071
Lucille 2!

23:39.112 --> 23:40.906
Help! Help!
Kevin, give me a hand!

23:40.947 --> 23:42.448
Get Dr. Bowman or Alicia.

23:42.490 --> 23:43.825
Either one.

23:43.867 --> 23:45.994
This woman's been
attacked by an ostrich!

23:46.036 --> 23:47.954
Ah, Tobias got a new girlfriend.

23:47.996 --> 23:49.246
(laughs)

23:52.792 --> 23:54.460
NARRATOR: Tobias had acted like
an actual superhero

23:54.502 --> 23:55.587
- and saved Lucille 2.
- There's my hero.

23:55.628 --> 23:57.089
You know, the doctor said

23:57.130 --> 23:58.381
if that bird had gotten through

23:58.423 --> 24:00.341
my second layer of makeup,
it could've done

24:00.383 --> 24:01.593
permanent damage to my skin.

24:01.634 --> 24:03.344
And I want to repay you.

24:03.386 --> 24:06.014
You're a doctor,
and you're out of work.

24:06.056 --> 24:07.933
- Well...
- How would you like to come work for me,

24:07.974 --> 24:09.392
at Austerity?

24:09.434 --> 24:11.436
The rehab center? That's yours?

24:11.477 --> 24:13.479
Well, my brother Argyle
runs it day to day.

24:13.521 --> 24:14.689
But we are so understaffed.

24:14.731 --> 24:16.191
You'd be such a gift.

24:16.233 --> 24:19.276
It would only pay
120 grand a year to start.

24:19.318 --> 24:21.529
Tobias, whose girlfriend
had nearly

24:21.571 --> 24:23.949
sold her body for money
in front of him,

24:23.990 --> 24:27.202
knew that everyone at some time
has to face reality.

24:27.244 --> 24:29.328
(sustained groaning)

24:31.372 --> 24:33.374
- But that this wasn't the time.
- No.

24:33.416 --> 24:35.127
- You turned it down?!
- Uh-huh.

24:35.168 --> 24:38.004
I almost (bleep) a guy
for a hamburger,

24:38.046 --> 24:40.924
and you turned down
$120, 000 a year?

24:40.966 --> 24:43.384
To keep our dream alive,
yes, I did.

24:43.426 --> 24:45.137
I thought you'd be proud of me.

24:45.178 --> 24:47.055
After all, a doctor in India

24:47.097 --> 24:49.641
told me that I have the gift
to make people laugh.

24:49.682 --> 24:51.308
- (sobbing)
- Why are you crying?

24:51.350 --> 24:53.394
(sobbing):
You're worse than Marky.

24:53.436 --> 24:57.398
He couldn't see me,
but you can't hear me.

24:57.440 --> 24:59.400
(sobbing)

24:59.442 --> 25:01.903
The setback sent
an emotionally fragile DeBrie

25:01.945 --> 25:04.614
back to her old ways.

25:04.656 --> 25:07.200
And before long,
she was picked up by a limo

25:07.242 --> 25:08.952
for a night of
being passed around

25:08.994 --> 25:11.412
amongst Hollywood creeps.

25:11.454 --> 25:15.458
For three weeks, Tobias waited,
hoping DeBrie would return.

25:15.500 --> 25:18.670
Perhaps it was
the morning he awoke to find

25:18.711 --> 25:20.255
two bums using him as a pillow

25:20.297 --> 25:22.465
that he realized
she wasn't coming back.

25:22.507 --> 25:24.050
Who are you supposed to be?

25:24.092 --> 25:26.552
Oh, I'm The Thing
from Fantastic Four.

25:26.594 --> 25:29.555
You've been served, (bleep).

25:29.597 --> 25:32.142
Oh, (bleep) me.

25:32.184 --> 25:33.977
Are you undercover as well?

25:34.019 --> 25:35.937
I'm CIA.
Not here for you though.

25:35.979 --> 25:38.315
Scoping out
Imagine Entertainment.

25:38.355 --> 25:40.733
So, with nowhere to go...

25:40.775 --> 25:42.443
Thought I'd try you again.

25:42.485 --> 25:44.154
...and no one to help him
out of his rock suit...

25:44.196 --> 25:46.281
Honey, you read
comic books, yes?

25:46.323 --> 25:47.824
...he went to see
if his daughter

25:47.866 --> 25:50.327
would give him a place to stay.

25:50.367 --> 25:52.495
(indistinct radio transmission)

25:52.537 --> 25:54.873
(singing quietly)

25:54.914 --> 25:57.667
Now the fun begins,
right, Officer Three?

25:57.709 --> 25:59.544
I'll say.

25:59.585 --> 26:02.130
...and why and how. Who, what,
when, where, why and how.

26:03.548 --> 26:06.301
Is there a little girl here
all by herself?

26:06.343 --> 26:08.636
And perhaps it was this
that would finally

26:08.678 --> 26:11.223
get him to admit
that he sometimes did speak

26:11.264 --> 26:12.932
in a misleading way.

26:12.974 --> 26:15.768
Daddy needs to get
his rocks off.

26:20.690 --> 26:23.235
BEARD: On the next
To Entrap a Local Predator...

26:23.276 --> 26:25.237
(high-pitched):
I'll be down in a minute.

26:25.278 --> 26:27.030
Have some lemonade.

26:27.072 --> 26:28.823
TV NARRATOR: Predator gets
its first rock-solid case.

26:28.865 --> 26:31.534
(normal voice):
Pretty good lemonade, huh?

26:31.576 --> 26:32.827
It is.

26:32.869 --> 26:34.537
Is there alcohol in here--
John Beard!

26:34.579 --> 26:35.538
Please, have a seat.

26:35.580 --> 26:36.539
Okay.

26:36.581 --> 26:37.707
Why are you here?

26:37.749 --> 26:39.125
I'm here to see my little girl.

26:39.167 --> 26:41.378
I wanted to show her
Daddy's Thing.

26:41.418 --> 26:42.712
What are you doing here?

26:42.754 --> 26:45.506
I'm doing a, um,
a local interest piece.

26:45.548 --> 26:46.507
Mm.

26:46.549 --> 26:47.592
Okay, get in there, boys.

26:47.633 --> 26:49.302
Oh, really local.

26:49.344 --> 26:50.345
That's right, yeah.

26:50.387 --> 26:51.428
Is this about my daughter?

26:51.470 --> 26:52.597
Oh, so it's your daughter

26:52.638 --> 26:54.307
- you're here to see?
- Yes.

26:55.058 --> 26:56.433
Maeby.

26:56.475 --> 26:58.311
If he's got a daughter,
then how old is she?

26:58.353 --> 26:59.436
BEARD:
Let me ask you this.

26:59.478 --> 27:00.437
How old is she?

27:00.479 --> 27:02.481
(chuckles):
Oh.

27:02.523 --> 27:04.359
Why do you put me on the spot?

27:04.401 --> 27:07.279
Um, I want to say 19?

27:07.320 --> 27:09.864
But I like
to think of her as 15.

27:09.906 --> 27:10.907
Well, you're free to go.

27:10.949 --> 27:12.533
She's not here.

27:12.575 --> 27:14.255
TV NARRATOR:
But this creep won't take "go"

27:14.286 --> 27:15.703
- for an answer.
- Oh, that's all right.

27:15.745 --> 27:17.289
I'll stay, I'll wait.

27:17.330 --> 27:19.291
And this creep makes himself
right at home.

27:19.332 --> 27:21.293
- Give me just a minute.
- He's not leaving.

27:21.334 --> 27:23.253
- He's not leaving.
- He's not leaving.

27:23.295 --> 27:25.171
Tell him there's a raccoon
in the backyard.

27:25.213 --> 27:26.756
Hey, guess what.

27:26.798 --> 27:28.549
There's a raccoon
out on the patio!

27:28.591 --> 27:29.617
Bull (bleep).

27:29.737 --> 27:30.907
Where is that little guy?

27:31.027 --> 27:33.805
And this guy turns out to be
a real comedian.

27:33.846 --> 27:34.635
(groans loudly)

27:34.755 --> 27:36.530
I just broke my skull
in a fourth place:

27:36.650 --> 27:38.134
the patio!

